## Design token system

All design values live as CSS custom properties in style.css :root.
All the same values are mirrored in theme.json for the block editor.
When updating tokens for a new project — update BOTH files.

### Key tokens

```
--color-primary        Headings, main text
--color-secondary      Supporting text
--color-accent         Links, buttons, highlights
--color-accent-hover   Hover state
--color-bg             Page background
--color-bg-alt         Cards, alternate sections
--color-bg-dark        Header, footer, dark sections
--color-text           Body text
--color-text-muted     Secondary text
--color-text-inverse   Text on dark backgrounds
--color-border         Borders, dividers, inputs

--font-body            Paragraph text, UI
--font-heading         H1-H6
--font-accent          Code, labels, mono

--text-xs through --text-4xl    Type scale
--space-1 through --space-24    Spacing scale
--radius-sm/md/lg/xl/full       Border radii
--shadow-sm/md/lg               Box shadows
--max-width                     1200px default
--wrapper-padding               40px default
```

---

## CSS rules — strictly enforced

```
ALWAYS:
- Use CSS tokens — var(--token-name) for all colors, spacing, radii, shadows
- Put block CSS inside the block folder only
- Put site-wide styles in style.css only
- Put per-template styles in a <style> block at the bottom of the template file

NEVER:
- Hardcode hex color values in any CSS file
- Hardcode pixel values when a token exists
- Use !important unless there is absolutely no alternative
- Create a new standalone CSS file outside of the block folder structure
```

---

## PHP conventions

```php
// Short echo tags — preferred
<?= $variable; ?>

// ACF field pattern
$title = get_field('field_name');
if ( $title ) : ?>
    <h2><?= $title; ?></h2>
<?php endif; ?>

// Always escape output
echo esc_html( $variable );
echo esc_url( $url );
echo esc_attr( $attribute );

// Repeater subfields
while ( have_rows('repeater_field') ) : the_row();
    $item = get_sub_field('sub_field_name');
endwhile;
```

---

## Block architecture

Every block follows the same 4-file pattern:

```
~wp_blocks/block-name/
├── block.json      ← Registration, metadata, ACF config
├── block-name.php  ← Render template, pulls ACF fields
├── block-name.css  ← Block styles using tokens only
└── block-name.js   ← Interactivity (only if needed)
```

All blocks are auto-registered via a glob loop in functions.php.

All 12 blocks use "category": "boilerplate-blocks" and appear under the "Boilerplate Blocks" group in the editor. Category registered via add_filter( 'block_categories_all' ) in functions.php.

### All 12 blocks — exact name values

NOTE: Block naming is inconsistent (known issue). Use exact values below.

| Folder | block.json name | Title |
|---|---|---|
| Hero/ | custom_hero | Hero |
| accordion/ | custom_accordion | Accordion |
| callout/ | custom_calloutBlock | Highlighted Content |
| contact_block/ | custom_contactBlock | Contact Us CTA |
| cta_banner/ | custom_cta_banner | CTA Banner |
| event/ | customEvent | Event |
| gallery/ | custom_gallery | Custom Gallery |
| page_list/ | custom_Page_List | Page Blocks |
| profiles_block/ | profilesBlock | Profiles |
| program/ | customProgram | Program |
| testimonials/ | custom_testimonials | Testimonials |
| video/ | custom_video | Video |

### Block CSS comment header — required on every block

```css
/*
==========================================================
BLOCK NAME — block-name.css
==========================================================
WHAT IT IS:
Brief description.

WHAT IT DOES:
Brief description.

HOW TO USE:
1. Step one
2. Step two

All values use boilerplate CSS tokens from style.css.
==========================================================
*/
```

